Function Reference/has filter « WordPress Codex
-----------

Check if any filter has been registered for a hook.

Usage
-----

`  <?php has_filter( $tag, $function_to_check ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$tag` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The name of the filter hook.
    Default: *None*

 `$function_to_check` 
:   ([*callback*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Callback "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) If specified, return the priority of that function on
    this hook or false if not attached.
    Default: False

Return
------

 int|boolean 
:   Optionally returns the priority on that hook for the specified
    function.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

-   Uses: global array `$wp_filter` that stores all of the filters

Change Log
----------

-   Since: 2.5.0

Source File
-----------

`has_filter()` is located in `wp-includes/plugin.php`.

